translations:
‘The
			horse began running in circles, from one side (of the house) to
			another and (thus) created wind and raised tumult’ 78/181;

‘The hen threw herself on the head of the snake. And she, the
			snake, coiled up (she was afraid of the hen) then turned around
			and moved quicql towards one of the chicken’ JL 13.11.8-9;
